AB  - Insect populations were sampled at regular intervals, by using Health light traps, throughout a 12 month period at various localities about Aldabra Atoll. Abundance and fluctuations in numbers throughout the year of the predominant orders, families and species of insects are given for localities on West, South and Middle Islands, and Ile Michel. Differences between the composition, diversity and density of insect populations at selected localities are discussed in relation to ecological factors such as vegetation, rainfall and the presence or absence of higher animals, in particular giant tortoises, Geochelone gigantea, and/or colonial breeding birds.
